Brazil,[b] officially the Federative Republic of Brazil,[c] is the
largest and easternmost country in South America. It is the world's
fifth-largest country by area and the seventh largest by population,
with over 212 million people. The country is a federation composed
of 26 states and a Federal District, which hosts the capital, Brasília.
Its most populous city is São Paulo, followed by Rio de Janeiro.
